    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "Despite the Not Accepted COU-level decision, the credibility assessment package itself is accepted as a complete and valid ASME V&V 40 submission artifact. The assessment correctly identifies all 13 credibility factors, documents achieved versus required levels, and flags 6 factors as epistemic gaps appropriate to MRL 5. The provenance chain supporting the synthesis evidence node is considered sufficiently documented by the assessment team based on narrative description of prior study aggregation. Monte Carlo UQ partial results are noted as a path forward. Submission accepted for regulatory review with conditions: complete UQ analysis, multi-model ensemble for model form, and inter-laboratory test sample reproducibility required prior to device clearance.",
    "decidedAt": "2026-04-19T00:00:00Z"
