      {
        "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/evidence/orphan-synthesis-node-001",
        "type": "Evidence",
        "name": "Synthesis of prior hemolysis modeling studies: power-law model parameter basis",
        "description": "This evidence node represents a comprehensive synthesis of seven published hemolysis modeling studies spanning 2004–2019, including Giersiepen et al. (1990), Wurzinger et al. (1985), Heuser and Opitz (1980), and four subsequent calibration studies on centrifugal pump geometries. The synthesis establishes the power-law exponent (α = 0.785) and coefficient (C = 3.62×10⁻⁵) used in the hemolysis transport model. The aggregated parameter set has been widely adopted in the CFD hemolysis literature and is considered a de facto standard for FDA generic pump benchmarking. The breadth and consistency of the underlying literature base provides high confidence in the parameter values without requiring re-derivation for this submission."
      },
